
!!page-heading < Nautilus >

Heading_1 < What is Project Nautilus? > {
It is a **network of several connected sub/mini projects** for building some solid fundamental skills and effective efficiency in various techinal fields.
}

Heading_2 < How It Works. > {
    It can be taken as a connection between multiple projects. A sub projects can talk to other projects and increase the efficiency of the final outcome. 
}


Heading_3 < Idea Behind the Project. > {
    A connection for projects to fetch or create a function much faster without having to rely or having complete dependance something that doesn't exists.

    !!center.small.line

    I created a first project local __**LLM**__ that does or executes a series of defined task on a computer.
    It worked out great, So I thought why not make it infinitely expandable using sub projects without making much changes in the __**LLM**__ project
}


